# Android — {{ project_name }}

Kotlin + Jetpack Compose with Clean Architecture (MVVM).

## Quick Reference

- **Build**: `./gradlew assembleDebug` (or `gradlew.bat` on Windows)
- **Test**: `./gradlew testDebugUnitTest`
- **Install**: `./gradlew installDebug`
- **Min SDK**: 29 | **Target SDK**: 35 | **Compile SDK**: 36

## Architecture

```
app/src/main/kotlin/{{ package_identifier | replace('.', '/') }}/
  app/             → Application + MainActivity
  core/
    common/        → AppResult, AppDispatchers
    session/       → SessionManager (interface + impl)
    network/       → ApiService, AuthInterceptor, TokenAuthenticator
    datastore/     → TokenStorage (DataStore)
    database/      → AppDatabase, Converters (shared only)
    di/            → NetworkModule, DatabaseModule, RepositoryModule, AppModule
    model/         → Cross-feature models: User, Session (AuthState), Paging
  navigation/      → Screen routes, NavGraph
  feature/
    auth/
      domain/      → AuthRepository interface, AuthCredentials model
      data/        → AuthDtos, AuthRepositoryImpl
      ui/          → SignInRoute, SignInScreen, SignInViewModel
    example/
      domain/      → ExampleRepository interface, Example model
      data/        → ExampleDtos, ExampleEntity, ExampleDao, Mappers, ExampleRepositoryImpl
      ui/          → ExampleListRoute, ExampleListScreen, ExampleListViewModel, components/
  designsystem/
    theme/         → Color, Type, Shape, Dimensions, Theme
    text/          → UiText (framework-light string wrapper)
    components/    → LoadingIndicator, ErrorView
```

## Patterns

- **ViewModel**: `@HiltViewModel` with `StateFlow<UiState>` (sealed interface co-located in ViewModel file)
- **Route/Screen split**: Route handles navigation wiring + ViewModel; Screen is a pure composable
- **Repository boundary**: Interface in `feature/*/domain/repository/`, impl in `feature/*/data/repository/`
- **DI**: Hilt — split modules: NetworkModule, DatabaseModule, RepositoryModule, AppModule
- **Session**: `SessionManager` exposes `StateFlow<AuthState>`, consumed by NavGraph
- **Token refresh**: `TokenAuthenticator` (OkHttp Authenticator) handles 401 → refresh → retry
- **Navigation**: Type-safe routes via `@Serializable` sealed interface

## Conventions

- Feature-specific persistence (Entity, DAO, Mappers) lives in `feature/*/data/local/`
- Shared database infrastructure (AppDatabase, Converters) lives in `core/database/`
- DTOs (`@Serializable`) in `feature/*/data/remote/dto/` — domain models are framework-light
- No use cases by default — add `usecase/` only when orchestration logic is needed
- `AppResult<T>` instead of `kotlin.Result` to avoid naming collision
- Tests: MockK + Turbine, test structure mirrors source
